author: Nicole Friedman
title: Oil Bears Aren’t Going Anywhere
text:
Oil investors and analysts argued all year about when in 2015 U.S. oil production would peak. Now that they know, market participants are no less divided on where prices are headed.
After months of sending mixed signals, federal data now definitively show that U.S. oil output peaked in April and has steadily fallen since.
